article.headline: N. Colorado 93, San Jose St. 69
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. -- Will Figures and Devon Beitzel scored 24 points each, leading Northern Colorado to a 93-69 victory over San Jose State Monday night. Neal Kingman added 11 for Northern Colorado (10-3). The Bears are out to their best start since opening 10-2 in 1988-89. Northern Colorado hit 18 of 37 from 3-point range, the most for the Bears this season. The previous best was 16. Adrian Oliver led San Jose State (5-5) with 26 points. C.J. Webster contributed 16 for the Spartans, who were denied their first three-game winning streak of the year. Oliver was coming off a 31-point game.
